ndation for future growth modules implemented in hpl are jd edwards financials management sales order management advanced pricing procurement management inventory management bulk stock management transportation management hpl has divided their operation in four line of business ie retail histreet lubricants and industrial business it is required to monitor profitability by line of business by customer and by product to cater their reporting needs a unique organizational structure is designed in jd edwards this structure includes four notational companies with respect to line of business which are consolidated in one parent company ie hascol petroleum to monitor petrol pump wise profitability a unique business unit is associated with each petrol which results in complete visibility in terms of cost and revenue  bulk stock management is designed specifically for oil  gas industry that handles the entire downstream bulk product supply and demand complexities our proposed solution enabled hpl to control all types of product movement including intradepot stock movements such as tanktotank transfers rebrands decanting blending and filling pinpoint inventory gains and losses before they become significant with flexible reconciliation capabilities automatically record inventory gains and losses occurs due to temperature variations project status completedproposed solution oracle jd edwards enterpriseonepriority  contact us email us salessystemsltdcom call sales      hascol petroleum ltd hascolkar profile  ftcom subscribe sign in menu search financial times myft search the ft search search the ft search close marketsmarkets dataequities financial timesclosesearch theftsearch equities hascol petroleum ltdhascolkarselect symbolpakistanhascolkarpakistan stock exchange ltdhascol petroleum ltdactionsadd to watchlistadd to portfolioadd an alertoil  gasoil  gas producersprice pkrtodays change  shares tradedk year changebetadata delayed at least  minutes as of aug    bstmore ▼applyc